Bachelor of Commerce

Bachelor of Commerce is a 3-year degree program. The Bachelor of Commerce degree is designed to provide students with a wide range of managerial skills, while building competence in a particular area of business. The B.Com. course list includes Marketing, Accounting, Entrepreneurship, various Taxation, and Industrial Laws, etc.

First Year Bachelor of Commerce

{/* First Semester */}

Semester I (F.Y.B.Com)

  • Accountancy & Financial Management I
  • Commerce I
  • Business Economics I
  • Business Communication I
  • Environmental Studies I
  • Foundation Course I
  • Mathematical and Statistical Techniques I
{/* Second Semester */}

Semester II (F.Y.B.Com)

  • Accountancy & Financial Management II
  • Commerce II
  • Business Economics II
  • Business Communication II
  • Environmental Studies II
  • Foundation Course II
  • Mathematical and Statistical Techniques II

Second Year Bachelor of Commerce

{/* Third Semester */}

Semester III (S.Y.B.Com)

  • Accountancy & Financial Management III
  • Discipline Specific Elective (Any One):
    • a) Financial Accounting and Auditing – Introduction to Management Accounting
    • b) Business Management – Marketing Management
  • Commerce III
  • Business Economics III
  • Skill Enhancement Course (Any One):
    • a) Advertising I
    • b) Co-operation I
{/* Fourth Semester */}

Semester IV (S.Y.B.Com)

  • Accountancy & Financial Management IV
  • Discipline Specific Elective (Any One):
    • a) Financial Accounting and Auditing – Auditing
    • b) Business Management – Marketing Management
  • Commerce IV
  • Business Economics IV
  • Skill Enhancement Course (Any One):
    • a) Advertising II
    • b) Co-operation II
  • Foundation Course

Third Year Bachelor of Commerce

{/* Fifth Semester */}

Semester V (T.Y.B.Com)

  • Discipline Specific Elective (Any One Group):
    • Group A – Advanced Accountancy:
      • a) Financial Accounting and Auditing – V: Financial Accounting
      • b) Financial Accounting and Auditing – VI: Cost Accounting
    • Group B – Business Management:
      • a) Business Management – V: Human Resource Management
      • b) Business Management – VI: Financial Management
  • Commerce V
  • Business Economics V
  • Direct and Indirect Taxation – I
  • Export Marketing – I
{/* Sixth Semester */}

Semester VI (T.Y.B.Com)

  • Discipline Specific Elective (Same Group as Semester V):
    • Group A – Advanced Accountancy:
      • a) Financial Accounting and Auditing – VII: Financial Accounting
      • b) Financial Accounting and Auditing – VIII: Auditing
    • Group B – Business Management:
      • a) Business Management – VII: Marketing Management
      • b) Business Management – VIII: Production Management
  • Commerce VI
  • Business Economics VI
  • Direct and Indirect Taxation – II
  • Export Marketing – II
